- Install a CentOS on a VM.
- Let the network use dhcp


Login and do the follow:
- Disable firewalld
  systemctl disable firewalld
- Disable SELinux
  edit /etc/selinux/config and set to disabled
- Edit /etc/hosts
  echo "172.0.0.1 centos.localdomain centos" >> /etc/hosts
- Update the system
  yum upgrade -y
- Install basic packages





- Convert it to template.
